On Wed, 31 Oct 2007 10:02:04 +0000, Zefram  wrote:

> Chaddaï Fouché wrote:
> >sub DESTROY {
> >   my $fh = shift;
> >   $fh->close() if $fh->opened();
> >}
> 
> If you're going to do that, make it:
> 
> sub DESTROY {
>    local($., $@, $!, $^E, $?);
                              , $^, $~, $-
>    my $fh = shift;
>    $fh->close() if $fh->opened();
> }
> 
> to avoid clobbering global status variables during unwinding.

-- 
